99% of my use of `satisfies` is to type-check exhaustivity in `switch` statements:    type Foo = 'foo' | 'bar';

    const myFoo: Foo = 'foo';
    switch (myFoo) {
      case 'foo':
        // do stuff
        break;
      default:
        myFoo satisfies never; // Error here because 'bar' not handled
    }reply
